ut agentlog show ...\n```\n\nLifecycle plumbing such as `hook` and `sync` may exist as hidden subcommands,\nbut they should not become the agent-facing context recovery workflow.\n\nThe command shape and argument mapping live in `but-agentlog`. The `but` crate\nshould remain limited to feature-gating, output mode selection, and delegation.\n\nWithout the `agentlog` feature, the command is not compiled\n[TRUNCATED]\n -> optionally add an explicit target association\n  -> return terse output\n```\n\nThe transcript parser should not write GitMeta. The GitMeta writer should not\nknow provider-specific transcript shapes beyond the normalized record it\nreceives.\n\n## Target And Associations\n\nThe durable session object should stay on the `project` target by default. Even\nwhen future code can identify a branch, change, commit, or pull request, those\nobjects should reference project session keys rather than own transcript data.\n\nThat keeps session handoff possible before code exists and avoids bad ownership\nguesses when one agent session contributes to multiple GitButler branches.\n\nRelationship keys look like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\n## GitMeta Writer\n\nThe writer is the only code that should open a `git_meta_lib::Session` or mutate\nGitMeta values. CLI code may parse an explicit association\n`git_meta_lib::Target` before calling the writer so target validation happens\nbefore repository side effects.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- open `git_meta_lib::Session`\n- write durable session data to `git_meta_lib::Target::project()`\n- maintain the project `gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>`\n- write session keys under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n- append redacted transcript records\n- deduplicate repeated capture with the session `:record-hashes` set\n- add `gitbutler:agent-sessions += <session-key>` to an explicit association\n  target when requested\n\nThe writer should return capture counts and never print.\n\n## Privacy Boundary\n\nCapture writes shareable-ready keys but does not publish them automatically.\n`but agentlog sync` is the manual exchange step; hook capture also invokes that\nsame command in the background after a successful capture.\n\nEven before publishing, transcripts are sensitive. The POC should redact copied\nstrings before storage and should not add full transcript paths, working\ndirectories, branch names, or raw provider session ids as normalized fields.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:40:50.667Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}